title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd')
OB: When opening the All types dialog in JDK 1.4, obfuscated classes (such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd') are displayed.
EB: When opening the All types dialog in JDK 1.4, obfuscated classes (such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd') should not be displayed.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Open the All types dialog in JDK 1.4. 2. Observe the presence of obfuscated classes (such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd').
